Vercel Speed Insights Installation
===================================

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the ResumeAI project.

## What was implemented:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 via npm
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with dependency tree

### 2. Frontend Integration
Added Vercel Speed Insights tracking scripts to both HTML pages:

**Modified Files:**
- `frontend/public/index.html` - Added Speed Insights script to landing page
- `frontend/public/builder.html` - Added Speed Insights script to builder page

**Implementation Details:**
- Added the Speed Insights initialization script in the `<head>` section of both HTML files
- Used the vanilla HTML/JavaScript integration method from the official Vercel documentation
- Script initializes the `window.si` function and loads the Speed Insights script from `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js`

### 3. Implementation Approach
Following the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart):
- For vanilla HTML/JavaScript projects, the integration uses a lightweight script loader
- The script is loaded asynchronously with the `defer` attribute to avoid blocking page rendering
- The Speed Insights script will automatically track Core Web Vitals metrics when deployed on Vercel

## Testing:

✅ Server starts successfully
✅ Health endpoint responds correctly
✅ Speed Insights scripts added to both HTML pages
✅ Package dependencies installed and lock file updated
✅ No lint errors (no linter configured)
✅ No test failures (no test suite configured)

## Next Steps:

To complete the Speed Insights setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard (Settings → Speed Insights → Enable)
3. Visit your deployed site to start collecting performance metrics
4. View metrics in the Vercel dashboard under Speed Insights

## Notes:

- This project is a Node.js/Express application serving static HTML files
- The integration follows the vanilla HTML/JavaScript pattern from the official documentation
- Speed Insights will automatically start tracking once the app is deployed and enabled in the Vercel dashboard
- The tracking script path `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js` is automatically served by Vercel's platform
